"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105841","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-04-05","<p>The UK is concerned about the restrictive practices imposed on independent media in Belarus. We continue to raise this issue as part of our ongoing bilateral dialogue with Belarus about human rights and democracy. Our Ambassador in Minsk most recently raised these issues with the Belarusian Deputy Foreign Minister in a meeting on 19 February 2019. The UK joined EU partners in raising concerns about the situation of Charter 97 during the EU-Belarus Human Rights dialogue on 17 July 2018. The UK is committed to the promotion of media freedom. The British Embassy in Minsk is working with NGOs in Belarus to implement projects to train independent journalists, build a media start-up accelerator, and arrange visits to share best practice with media counterparts in the UK.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2019-04-05T12:46:28.897Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105841/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105841/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105841/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-03-28","Belarus: Mass Media","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department plans to take in response to the censoring of website and news outlet Charter 97 by Belarusian authorities; and what support his Department provides to independent news sources in Belarusian society.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","238382"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105842","Department for Education","false","2019-04-05","<p>I refer the hon. Member for Bury North to the answer I gave on 1 April 2019 to Question <a href="https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2019-03-26/237114/" target="_blank">237114</a>.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2019-04-05T12:30:58.617Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105842/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105842/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105842/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-03-28","Children: Social Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what data his Department collects to monitor the effectiveness of early years intervention strategies in (a) each local authority area, (b) each regional area and (c) England.","true","Biography information for James Frith","Bury North","James Frith","238383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105843","Department for Transport","false","2019-04-02","<p>The transparency data for financial transactions over £25,000 for October, November and December 2018 was published on 28 March 2019 on GOV.UK</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2019-04-02T10:24:48.057Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105843/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105843/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105843/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-03-28","Department for Transport: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, for what reason his Department has not published the transparency data entitled Dft: Spending over £25,000 for the months of (a) October, (b) November and (c) December 2018; and when he plans to publish those documents.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","238373"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105844","Department for Transport","false","2019-04-04","<p>The Bus Services Act 2017 includes powers for the Secretary of State to make Regulations requiring bus operators to provide audible and visible information on local bus services in Great Britain.</p><p> </p><p>The Government understands the importance of accessible on-board information in helping bus passengers to travel with confidence, and in Summer 2018 published a public consultation on proposals to require its provision on local bus services throughout Great Britain. This follows the Government’s commitment, set out in the Inclusive Transport Strategy, to invest £2 million towards ensuring that audio visual equipment is installed on buses.</p><p> </p><p>We continue to analyse responses to the consultation and expect to announce our next steps regarding the making of Regulations and publication of guidance later in the year.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2019-04-04T12:59:56.987Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105844/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105844/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105844/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-03-28","Bus Services: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress his Department has made to ensure that all bus operators are providing audio visual (AV) next stop and final destination announcements as required under the Bus Services Act 2017; and what steps his Department is taking to make bus transport more accessible for disabled people.","false","Biography information for Maggie Throup","Erewash","Maggie Throup","238384"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105845","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-04-04","<p>My rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State continues to discuss the timing of a debate on these Regulations with Cabinet colleagues, including the Leader of the House.</p>","Rochester and Strood","Kelly Tolhurst",,"2019-04-04T15:13:00.42Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105845/answer","Biography information for Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105845/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105845/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-03-28","State Aid (EU Exit) Regulations 2019","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether he has had discussions with the Leader of the House on a new date for bringing forward his Department's State Aid (EU Exit) Regulations 2019.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","238331"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105846","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-04-02","<p>As set out in the 2015 Strategic Defence and Security Review, the UK and France have the full range of military capabilities and the political will to protect our interests globally. We have built an exceptionally close defence and security relationship with France through the Lancaster House Treaty of 2010. Our Armed Forces routinely work together and with the US in NATO, the Middle East, Africa, Asia and the Caribbean.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2019-04-02T15:05:56.1Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105846/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105846/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105846/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-03-28","Defence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the value of partnering with the French Government in the development of the UK's military capability.","true","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","238346"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105847","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-04-04","<p>No assessment has been made of the correlation between asthma and academic performance in children.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2019-04-04T12:37:37.487Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105847/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105847/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105847/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-03-28","Education: Asthma","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, with reference to the study published in Annals of Allergy, Asthma and Immunology entitled Asthma and Academic Performance in Urban Children, what assessment he has made of the correlation between asthma and academic performance in children; and what steps he is taking to improve asthma control among children living in urban areas.","false","Biography information for Paul Farrelly","Newcastle-under-Lyme","Paul Farrelly","238282"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105848","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-04-04","<p>While the Ministry of Justice collects statistics about the number of writs that are received and enforced, either in full or in part, by High Court Enforcement Officers, it does not monitor the timeliness with which a High Court Enforcement Officer or company reclaims moneys awarded through a court judgment.</p><p>Complaints about a High Court Enforcement Officer can be made to the company employing the High Court Enforcement Officer or to the High Court Enforcement Officers’ Association. Unfortunately, the court cannot guarantee that a creditor will reclaim the payment of a civil judgment, particularly where a debtor goes to great lengths to evade payment or simply does not have the means to pay.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer","238386","2019-04-04T16:43:02.763Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105848/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105848/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105848/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-03-28","High Court Enforcement: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps his Department is taking to monitor the timeliness with which High Court Enforcement Ltd reclaim moneys awarded through a court judgment.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","238385"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105849","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-04-04","<p>While the Ministry of Justice collects statistics about the number of writs that are received and enforced, either in full or in part, by High Court Enforcement Officers, it does not monitor the timeliness with which a High Court Enforcement Officer or company reclaims moneys awarded through a court judgment.</p><p>Complaints about a High Court Enforcement Officer can be made to the company employing the High Court Enforcement Officer or to the High Court Enforcement Officers’ Association. Unfortunately, the court cannot guarantee that a creditor will reclaim the payment of a civil judgment, particularly where a debtor goes to great lengths to evade payment or simply does not have the means to pay.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer","238385","2019-04-04T16:43:02.827Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105849/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105849/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105849/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-03-28","Judgements: Enforcement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what guidance his Department issued to claimants who wish to make a complaint in the event that moneys owed to them through a court judgment are not reclaimed in full by high court enforcement companies.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","238386"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105850","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-04-02","<p>The Commission on Human Medicines (CHM) advises health ministers on the safety, efficacy and quality of medicinal products. Expert Working Groups of the CHM are comprised of independent experts who work on a voluntary basis and receive reasonable expenses. The Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency provide a secretariat function to the CHM and its Expert Working Groups. This is included in Agency costs. The Agency is an Executive Agency of the Department and it is established as a Government trading fund, with its work predominantly funded by fees charged to the industry it regulates.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2019-04-02T16:08:11.597Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105850/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105850/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105850/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-03-28","Pregnancy Tests","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how much was spent from the public purse on the Commission on Human Medicines Expert Working Group on Hormone Pregnancy Tests.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","238314"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105851","Department for Transport","false","2019-04-02","<p>The Government’s consultation response on bus open data explains that the Government will bring forward a statutory instrument later this year which will require bus operators in England to publish various forms of data.</p><p> </p><p>The key requirements are for data on routes and timetables to be published from January 2020; real time information and simple fares by January 2021; and complex fares by January 2023. The difference between simple and complex fares is explained in section 4 of the consultation response.</p><p> </p><p>To support this, the response also explains that the Government is developing a Bus Open Data Digital Service, which will allow app developers to access all of the information in a machine-readable format. We are currently developing the digital service and expect it to be available for use by all bus operators towards the end of the summer.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2019-04-02T11:43:44.987Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105851/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105851/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105851/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-03-28","Bus Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to the document entitled Bus Services Act 2017: Bus Open Data Consultation Response: Moving Britain Ahead, published by his Department in January 2019, when he plans to publish the steps his Department will take in response to the responses received to that consultation.","false","Biography information for Mr Mark Prisk","Hertford and Stortford","Mr Mark Prisk","238281"
